Stage 1
---
docker build -t hello-go .
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 --name hello-go-app hello-go:latest
Now you will be able to access hello world wep page throw below link
http://127.0.0.1:8080
-------------------
Stage 2
---
Now let's push this image to our github registry 
docker push username/hello-go:latest
for examole 
docker push amrmohamady/hello-go:latest
----------------------------
Stage 3
---
Deploying to Kubernetes cluster
kubectl create -f go-app.yml
kubectl get deployments
kubectl get pods
kubectl get svc
----------------------------
Stage 4
---
Testing - access the app
Go to browser with your cluster master ip:nodePort


Great! Now we've just deployed our go application to Kubernetes cluster


